Subject: devfs on 2.4.0-test4 - /proc/ide not consistant with /dev/ide
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2000/7/27/42

The following shows how the devices for my IDE hard drive as shown in /dev
and /proc/partitions are not consistant with /proc/ide .
This confuses noflushd and may confuse other software too.
I believe that the /proc/ide tree should match /dev/ide, so there should be
/proc/ide/host0/bus0/...
Russell Coker
rjc@lyta:/proc/ide/ide0$l
total 4
dr-xr-xr-x    3 root     root            0 Jul 27 15:55 .
dr-xr-xr-x    3 root     root            0 Jul 27 15:37 ..
-r--r--r--    1 root     root            0 Jul 27 15:55 channel
-rw-r--r--    1 root     root            0 Jul 27 15:55 config
dr-xr-xr-x    2 root     root            0 Jul 27 15:55 hda
-r--r--r--    1 root     root            0 Jul 27 15:55 mate
-r--r--r--    1 root     root            0 Jul 27 15:55 model
rjc@lyta:/proc/ide/ide0$cat /proc/partitions
major minor  #blocks  name
   3     0    9820440 ide/host0/bus0/target0/lun0/disc
   3     1     309959 ide/host0/bus0/target0/lun0/part1
   3     2      22680 ide/host0/bus0/target0/lun0/part2
   3     3    1239840 ide/host0/bus0/target0/lun0/part3
   3     4          1 ide/host0/bus0/target0/lun0/part4
   3     5    2268000 ide/host0/bus0/target0/lun0/part5
